## Context

Ticket 0118 (PR #764) fixed `compute_s4_frechet` returning a 0-column DataFrame when
`_iter_window_pairs` yields no pairs (empty `results` list). The root cause was:

```python
return pd.DataFrame(results)   # pd.DataFrame([]) has 0 columns, not the schema columns
```

followed by the dispatcher's `result["channel"] = channel` producing a 1-column `['channel']`
DataFrame that fails `DivergenceSchema.validate`.

Tickets 0120 adds the guard to 7 more functions. But without a standing regression test, the same
anti-pattern can silently re-enter any compute module in a future PR.

## The class to cover

Any function registered in `compute_divergence.METHODS` must return a DataFrame whose columns
are either:
  - the full DivergenceSchema columns (`year`, `window`, `hyperparams`, `value`, `channel`), or
  - `empty_divergence_df()` columns (`year`, `window`, `hyperparams`, `value`) â€” empty is ok

A DataFrame with only `['channel']` (or no columns at all) is a contract violation.

## Actions

Write a parametrized test in `tests/test_divergence.py` or a new `tests/test_dispatcher_contract.py`:

```python
@pytest.mark.parametrize("method", list(METHODS.keys()))
def test_dispatcher_result_columns_on_tiny_corpus(method, tmp_path):
    """compute_divergence.py must emit valid-schema CSV even on a 1-row corpus."""
    # Build a tiny fixture: 1-row works CSV with required columns, no embeddings needed
    # Run compute_divergence.py --method M --output tmp/out.csv with that corpus
    # Assert: output CSV has columns matching DivergenceSchema (year, window, hyperparams, value, channel)
    # OR has 0 rows (empty is fine; malformed is not)
```

The test should be `@pytest.mark.slow` (runs the script as subprocess). It validates the dispatcher
contract, not the statistical output â€” so a 1-row corpus that produces 0 divergence rows is a
PASS; a SchemaError or a 1-column `['channel']` CSV is a FAIL.

## Exit criteria

- [ ] Test exists and passes for all methods in `METHODS.keys()`
- [ ] Test is marked `@pytest.mark.slow` (excluded from check-fast)
- [ ] `make check-fast` clean

